column3: Greetings and welcome to the Athenaeum Astrologicum. Might I ask what drew you here to this place of learning?
You could not be more correct. For in the stars are written the fates of every woman and man on Hydaelyn.
As are all of us until we learn to open our eyes and see the answers which lie above us in the boundless firmament.

And it was there in the stars that I read a \x02\x08\x0f\xe9\x05\xff\x06woman\xff\x04man\x03 would call upon the Athenaeum this very day. A \x02\x08\x0f\xe9\x05\xff\x06woman\xff\x04man\x03 who would play an important role in \x02\x1a\x02\x02\x03my\x02\x1a\x02\x01\x03 own life.
Ah, but my apologies. Even the most skilled reader cannot scry a name from the heavens. Would you be so kind as to give me yours, so that I might know who is to be my newest prot\xc3\xa9g\xc3\xa9?
Give Jannequinard your name and become his prot\xc3\xa9g\xc3\xa9?

\x02,\r\xff\x07\x02)\x03\xeb\x02\x03\xff\x02 \x02\x03. Well... I was not expecting that. But what is a name, but an attempt by our begetters to wield power over the lives of their sons and daughters? Lives whose paths have already been foretold! In a sense, that is.

My name is Jannequinard de Durendaire and I am an astrologian for the Holy See. Remember that name, for it shall echo forevermore in the annals of Ishgardian history. Well...it will once I put it there. Once \x02\x1a\x02\x02\x03we\x02\x1a\x02\x01\x03 put it there!

Well...er... That was awkward. It would not be entirely true if I said this was the first time my offer had been spurned today... But Twelve be damned, I was certain you were the \x02\x08\x0f\xe9\x05\xff\x06woman\xff\x04man\x03 from my vision!
